# 2.2.a
a = StarWarsDF.groupby('How much do you like Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace?').Age.value_counts()
import numpy as np
x = np.arange(4)
x_lab = ['> 60', '45-60', '30-44', '18-29']
b = [a[1]['> 60'], a[1]['45-60'], a[1]['30-44'], a[1]['18-29']]
plt.bar(x+0.0, b, width=0.1, label='Rating 1')
c = [a[2]['> 60'], a[2]['45-60'], a[2]['30-44'], a[2]['18-29']]
plt.bar(x+0.1, c, width=0.1, color='g', label='Rating 2')
d = [a[3]['> 60'], a[3]['45-60'], a[3]['30-44'], a[3]['18-29']]
plt.bar(x+0.2, d, width=0.1, color='r', label='Rating 3')
e = [a[4]['> 60'], a[4]['45-60'], a[4]['30-44'], a[4]['18-29']]
plt.bar(x+0.3, e, width=0.1, color='y', label='Rating 4')
f = [a[5]['> 60'], a[5]['45-60'], a[5]['30-44'], a[5]['18-29']]
plt.bar(x+0.4, f, width=0.1, color='pink', label='Rating 5')
g = [a[6]['> 60'], a[6]['45-60'], a[6]['30-44'], a[6]['18-29']]
plt.bar(x+0.5, g, width=0.1, color='orange', label='Rating 6')
plt.legend(loc = (1.1, 0.5))
plt.xticks(x+0.3, x_lab)
plt.title("Rating to StarWars 1 according to age group.", fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel('Age Groups')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.show()
